idering whether we can reach the class directly through its literal. We can use `CustomFileAccess.class.getName()` to make it accessible but it might not be reflectively instantiable right away. I wonder if the Native Image might support reflection if `Class.getConstructor` is constant-folded, but the code within the library might not be constant due to a property string. This could lead to tests failing natively if metadata is missing, unless the agent generated the necessary config conditionally.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring test class challenges**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the test class is possible since user classes aren't included in the library metadata. For native tests, it seems that the TCK might run an agent on the tests before compiling natively, which should be okay. I might need to utilize the existing FileAccess implementation to dodge issues with reflection regarding test class metadata. There’s also org.hsqldb.lib.FileUtil to consider, but it requires a constructor with Object and FileAccess. I’ll have to search for classes implementing FileAccess.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_k8WgDTdM5NpPwMr0i87lEnNv|fc_0b970ea41f9f2f0f0169f911e92f6881959402a86aa2d82fc1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"implements FileAccess|class .*FileAccess\" -n /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/main/extracted/org/hsqldb | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 295, "output": 1210, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25057, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777930707852, "responseId": "resp_0b970ea41f9f2f0f0169f911d44ea08195bf2d3fd05a416932"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_k8WgDTdM5NpPwMr0i87lEnNv|fc_0b970ea41f9f2f0f0169f911e92f6881959402a86aa2d82fc1", "too